            </div>
            <div><h2>-------->Flask</h2><br>
                <p>Flask is a micro web framework written in Python. It is classified as a microframework because it does not require particular tools or libraries.It has no database abstraction layer, form validation, or any other components where pre-existing third-party libraries provide common functions.</p>
                <br>
                <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flask_(web_framework)#:~:text=Flask%20is%20a%20micro%20web,party%20libraries%20provide%20common%20functions.">Learn more-></a>


            </div>
            <div><h2>--------->Harcscade</h2><br>
                <p>Haar cascade is an algorithm that can detect objects in images, irrespective of their scale in image and location. This algorithm is not so complex and can run in real-time. We can train a haar-cascade detector to detect various objects.</p>
                <br>
                <a href="https://docs.opencv.org/3.4/db/d28/tutorial_cascade_classifier.html">Learn more-></a>
